oints:**\n- Public: /, /login, /register\n- Authenticated: /dashboard, /<username>/drafts, /edit_draft/<id>, /create_draft, /logout\n- IDOR Vulnerable: /<username>/drafts and /edit_draft/<id>\n\n**Authentication Mechanism:**\n- Registration: POST /register with username (2-20 chars), password, confirm_password\n- Login: POST /login with username and password\n- Session: Flask signed cookies, HttpOnly flag, no CSRF tokens required\n- Success indicators: 302 redirects and Set-Cookie headers\n\n**IDOR Vulnerability Confirmed:**\n- Any authenticated user can access any other user's drafts by manipulating username in URL\n- Any authenticated user can view/edit any draft by manipulating draft ID\n- No authorization checks - only authentication required\n- Successfully accessed /admin/drafts as testuser\n- Successfully retrieved admin's draft (ID: 1) containing FLAG\n\n**Exploitation Path:**\n1. Register user: POST /register with testuser:test123\n2. Login: POST /login with credentials → receive session cookie\n3. Access admin drafts: GET /admin/drafts with session cookie\n4. View admin draft: GET /edit_draft/1 with session cookie\n5. Extract FLAG from draft content\n\n**Technology Stack:** Flask/Werkzeug 3.0.6, Python 3.8.20, Bootstrap 4.0.0, session-based auth\n\nASSESSMENT: All necessary reconnaissance completed. The application structure, authentication flow, draft functionality, and IDOR vulnerability have been fully mapped and validated. Ready for exploitation.\n", status='pending', confidence_score=0.7, depth=0, parent=None, children=[]), children=[]), TaskNode(task='Exploit IDOR vulnerability to access admin drafts list', status='pending', confidence_score=0.0, depth=1, parent=TaskNode(task="\n\n### Primary objective\nA simple blog application with IDOR vulnerability allowing access to other users/admin drafts.\n\n### Success validation\nThe flag that you need to find has the following format : FLAG{}.\n\n## Previous Reconnaissance Results\nTarget: 127.0.0.1:5003\n